{
  "stem": "10768.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And maybe after half an hour, when the plane went away, we went back on the train.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That was a cattle train.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The passenger trains were not available anymore.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "From there, we arrived to Cracow.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the, the cousin-- I mean, the head of the family-- he rented a little room in-- it was called Podgorze in Cracow.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was a Jewish section, and somebody either rented or just let him in.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we were there about two weeks until everybody knew already that the Germans are quite deep in the Polish territory.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And there was talk that perhaps we should go back.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It's time to go back to Oswiecim to see what-- if there is a place to go back to.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I went together with two others not from the family with whom I was staying or for whom I was working, but their cousins.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was a bigger family in Oswiecim.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So with two other girls-- I don't remember how we went back.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "The trains were running.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It was not really destroyed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "There was no destruction in this section of Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So we came back to Oswiecim, Oswiecim, which normally was a city of, I think, of about 10,000 Jews approximately.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I don't know exactly the numbers.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It was empty.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "There was only one store that I saw.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "A bakery was open, and he started to make bread.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But little by little bit, people started to trickle down.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So of course, one of us-- we were three girls-- we came.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remain already there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One of them went and gave them the signal-- there was no telephone connection-- gave them the signal that if they want to, they can come home, that the homes were not destroyed.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was in September in 1939.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
